title: United Kingdom ( UK ) property market 2013 - 2016 , by submarket value
summary: This grouped bar chart shows Submarket value in billion GBP on the Y-axis for 5 different Submarkets for 4 groups 2013, 2014, 2015, and 2016 that are presented on the X-axis.

Out of all 4 groups, 2016 had the highest Submarket value in billion GBP in Submarket Residential property: owner occupied & social housing and 2013 had the lowest Submarket value in billion GBP in Submarket Infrastructure.

Among all the Submarkets, 2013 had the highest Submarket value in billion GBP in Submarket Residential property: owner occupied & social housing and lowest Submarket value in billion GBP in Submarket Infrastructure.
Submarket Residential property: owner occupied & social housing and Infrastructure had the biggest gap of 3830.0 between the highest and lowest Submarket value in billion GBP found for 2013.
